/*
:name: bad_if
:type: error
:error: end the statement
*/

// `i c` is junk before a `{ … }` block — almost certainly a typo for an `if`
// (`if c { … }`). tree-sitter parks `i c` in an ERROR node and recovers at the
// `{`, so the file used to "parse fine" and silently drop the stray tokens.
// A statement-position ERROR node must be reported as a syntax error.
i c { // locate_error_here
  cputs("hello {c}")
}
